---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Fisher & Paykel Appliance Repair Los Angeles | DishDrawer & DCS Specialists";
const description = "Expert Fisher & Paykel appliance repair in Los Angeles. DishDrawer, CoolDrawer, DCS ranges, ActiveSmart refrigerators. Same-day service, OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Fisher & Paykel Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-fisher-paykel-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Fisher & Paykel Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Fisher & Paykel DishDrawer Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Fisher & Paykel CoolDrawer Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"DCS Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Fisher & Paykel Washer Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Fisher & Paykel Oven Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Fisher & Paykel appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Fisher & Paykel repairs run $165–$580. DishDrawer drawer mechanism service, water inlet valve replacement, or seal work is on the lower end. Control board or sealed system work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Fisher & Paykel DishDrawer dishwashers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — DishDrawer is our most common Fisher & Paykel service call. The drawer mechanism (the slide and latch system that opens and seals each drawer) is the most frequent failure point — it operates differently from standard dishwasher door systems and requires specific knowledge. We stock common DishDrawer drawer mechanism components and carry them on the truck."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair the Fisher & Paykel CoolDrawer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The CoolDrawer's five-mode temperature system (freezer, chill, fridge, pantry, wine) is unique in the refrigeration market. Common failures: the mode selector not transitioning between temperatures, temperature drift in a specific mode, and the drawer seal system. We service the full CoolDrawer including the temperature control circuit and drawer mechanism."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair DCS ranges and cooking appliances?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. DCS is Fisher & Paykel's professional cooking brand. DCS ranges are designed to bring commercial kitchen power to residential settings — dual-flow burners, heavy-duty grates, infrared broilers. Common issues: igniter failure, gas valve faults, oven temperature calibration. We service the full DCS product line including indoor ranges and outdoor grills."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Fisher & Paykel ActiveSmart technology and how does it fail?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ActiveSmart is Fisher & Paykel's refrigerator intelligence system — it monitors door openings, ambient temperature, and food load to automatically adjust cooling. When the ActiveSmart sensor or control module fails, the refrigerator runs at a fixed cooling rate regardless of actual conditions, causing temperature fluctuations and increased energy consumption. Sensor replacement resolves most ActiveSmart failures."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Fisher & Paykel owned by Haier?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — Haier acquired 90% of Fisher & Paykel in 2012. For repair purposes this means current F&P appliances have access to Haier's supply chain, which improves parts availability for newer models. Legacy Fisher & Paykel appliances (pre-2012) use original F&P components available through the established service network."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .brand-family { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .brand-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
  .brand-card.featured { background: #1a0505; }
  .brand-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .brand-card.featured .brand-name { color: var(--red); }
  .brand-role { font-size: 11px; color: #666; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }
  .tip-nz { border-color: #2a7a4a; background: #f0fff5; }
  .tip-nz .tip-label { color: #2a7a4a; }

  .modes-strip { display: flex; gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 20px; }
  .mode-card { flex: 1; background: #161616; padding: 14px 12px; text-align: center; }
  .mode-temp { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .mode-name { font-size: 11px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-drawer { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-dcs { background: #555; }
  .tag-la { background: #5a2a7a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .brand-family { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .modes-strip { flex-direction: column; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Fisher &amp; Paykel Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        F&amp;P Repair.<br/>
        <span>DishDrawer.</span><br/>
        DCS. CoolDrawer.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Fisher &amp; Paykel invented the DishDrawer in the 1990s and changed how kitchens work. The CoolDrawer refrigerator with five temperature modes. DCS professional ranges for serious home cooks. We repair all of it — including the drawer mechanisms that no standard appliance company has ever seen.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">Same</div><div class="badge-label">Day Service</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">OEM</div><div class="badge-label">F&amp;P Parts</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">90-Day</div><div class="badge-label">Warranty</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">$89</div><div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">DishDrawer Drawer Mechanism Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">DCS Range Repair</span>
    <span class="trust-item">CoolDrawer Five-Mode Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Fisher &amp; Paykel</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">New Zealand Innovation That Redesigned the Kitchen</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Fisher &amp; Paykel was founded in 1934 in Auckland, New Zealand — originally as an importer of refrigerators and washing machines. By the 1990s they were inventing products that didn't exist before: the DishDrawer in 1996, a two-drawer dishwasher that let you run each drawer independently and changed how people thought about kitchen workflow. The CoolDrawer followed — a single drawer unit with five selectable temperature modes, from freezer to wine cellar, that could be installed anywhere in the kitchen or home.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Fisher &amp; Paykel also owns the DCS brand — professional-grade cooking equipment originally designed for commercial kitchens, now available for residential installation. DCS ranges bring dual-flow burners, heavy-duty continuous grates, and infrared broilers to home kitchens that want commercial performance without the compromise. Since 2012, Haier holds 90% of Fisher &amp; Paykel, which has improved supply chain access for newer model parts while legacy F&amp;P components remain available through the established service network.
    </p>

    <div class="brand-family">
      <div class="brand-card featured"><div class="brand-name">Fisher &amp; Paykel</div><div class="brand-role">Founded 1934 · Auckland, NZ</div></div>
      <div class="brand-card"><div class="brand-name">DCS</div><div class="brand-role">Professional Cooking · F&amp;P Sub-Brand</div></div>
      <div class="brand-card"><div class="brand-name">Haier</div><div class="brand-role">90% Owner Since 2012 · Parts Access</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-nz" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🥝 The Drawer Philosophy</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Fisher &amp; Paykel's drawer-based products — DishDrawer and CoolDrawer — reflect a design philosophy of bringing appliances to the user rather than requiring the user to reach into a fixed box. The DishDrawer runs each drawer as an independent dishwasher: run the top drawer for a small load while the bottom waits, or run both simultaneously for a full load. The CoolDrawer goes anywhere in the kitchen — under a counter, in an island, beside a wine rack — because it's a drawer, not a box that needs clearance to open. These products require different service knowledge than standard appliances.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Fisher &amp; Paykel Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All F&amp;P and DCS models, same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">DishDrawer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Single and Double DishDrawer models across all generations (DD24, DD60, DD90 series). The drawer slide mechanism and drawer latch seal are the most distinctive failure points — they operate differently from any standard dishwasher door system. Each drawer is an independent wash zone with its own pump, water inlet, and control circuit. We diagnose by drawer, not by machine.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: drawer mechanism stiff or stuck · drawer seal failure · one drawer works, other doesn't · not draining · not cleaning · control board · water inlet · pump motor · door latch</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">CoolDrawer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">The CoolDrawer's five temperature modes — freezer (-7°F), chill (23°F), fridge (37°F), pantry (55°F), wine (62°F) — are controlled by a dedicated mode selector and temperature circuit. When a mode fails to maintain its target temperature, or the drawer won't transition between modes, the cause is usually the temperature sensor or the mode control board rather than the compressor.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: mode not transitioning · temperature drift in specific mode · freezer mode not reaching target · drawer seal worn · compressor · temperature sensor · control board · drawer mechanism</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">DCS Range &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">DCS professional-style ranges (DS, RDV series) and gas cooktops. DCS dual-flow burners — a patented system that delivers flame both from the top and sides of the burner cap for more even heat — require specific OEM components when igniters fail. The DCS infrared broiler system is also a distinct service area. We carry DCS-specific igniter and broiler components.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: dual-flow igniter failure · burner not lighting · DCS infrared broiler · oven temperature off · door gasket · control board · gas valve · continuous grate damage</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌀</div>
        <div class="service-name">Washer &amp; Dryer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Fisher &amp; Paykel front-load and top-load washers, and matching dryers. F&amp;P laundry appliances have specific service requirements — particularly their GWL series top-loaders with the Phase 7 motor that doesn't use a traditional belt. SmartDrive motor failures present differently than belt-drive failures and require F&amp;P-specific diagnostic approach.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: SmartDrive motor fault · not spinning · not draining · door latch · bearing failure · control board · error codes · dryer not heating · thermal fuse</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🧠</div>
        <div class="service-name">ActiveSmart Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">F&amp;P ActiveSmart refrigerators use a sensor system that monitors door openings and ambient temperature to optimize cooling. Standard French door, counter-depth, and column models. When the ActiveSmart module fails, the refrigerator runs at a fixed cooling rate that doesn't adapt to actual conditions — temperature fluctuations result. We test the ActiveSmart sensor and the control module separately.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: ActiveSmart sensor failure · temperature fluctuation · not cooling · ice maker · water dispenser · door gasket · condenser service · compressor · defrost system</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Oven, Cooktop &amp; Ventilation Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">F&amp;P wall ovens, the "Gas on Glass" cooktop (gas burners on a sealed glass surface — a design that creates specific cleaning and service requirements), and ventilation hoods. The Gas on Glass cooktop's sealed glass surface means igniter failure presents differently than standard cast-iron burner configurations — the igniter geometry is specific to the glass-mounted burner design.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: Gas on Glass igniter failure · oven not heating · temperature sensor · convection fan · door gasket · ventilation motor · cooktop control board · hood motor</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:32px">
      <h3 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--text)">CoolDrawer Temperature Modes</h3>
      <div class="modes-strip">
        <div class="mode-card"><div class="mode-temp">−7°F</div><div class="mode-name">Freezer</div></div>
        <div class="mode-card"><div class="mode-temp">23°F</div><div class="mode-name">Chill</div></div>
        <div class="mode-card"><div class="mode-temp">37°F</div><div class="mode-name">Fridge</div></div>
        <div class="mode-card"><div class="mode-temp">55°F</div><div class="mode-name">Pantry</div></div>
        <div class="mode-card"><div class="mode-temp">62°F</div><div class="mode-name">Wine</div></div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;">Each mode is a distinct temperature target maintained by the CoolDrawer's control circuit. Mode-specific failures — where the unit holds temperature in some modes but not others — indicate a temperature sensor calibration issue, not a compressor failure.</p>
