    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Fisher &amp; Paykel Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does Fisher &amp; Paykel appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Most F&amp;P repairs run $165–$580. DishDrawer latch seal or drain pump service is on the lower end. SmartDrive motor or control board work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do you repair Fisher &amp; Paykel DishDrawer dishwashers?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes — DishDrawer is our most common F&amp;P service call. We diagnose by drawer zone, not by machine — each drawer is independent with its own pump, water inlet, and control circuit. The drawer latch seal and slide mechanism are the most distinctive failure points. We carry DishDrawer components and service all DD24, DD60, and DD90 series models.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can you repair the CoolDrawer's five-mode temperature system?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. Mode-specific failure — where some temperature modes work and others don't — is almost always a temperature sensor calibration issue in the failing mode's range, not a compressor problem. We test each mode independently and replace only the sensor if that's the fault. Most CoolDrawer temperature problems are resolved without compressor work.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do you repair DCS ranges?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. DCS is Fisher &amp; Paykel's professional cooking brand. We service DCS gas and dual-fuel ranges, cooktops, and outdoor equipment. DCS dual-flow burners require OEM geometry-specific igniters — we carry them. Common issues: dual-flow igniter failure, oven temperature calibration, and DCS infrared broiler faults.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is ActiveSmart and can you repair it?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. ActiveSmart is F&amp;P's adaptive refrigerator control system that monitors door openings and ambient temperature to optimize cooling. When the sensor module fails, the refrigerator reverts to fixed-cycle operation — causing cold spots and warm zones. Sensor module replacement (OEM) restores adaptive function. We test the adaptive response after replacement before leaving.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can you diagnose the SmartDrive washer motor?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes — and this requires F&amp;P-specific diagnostic equipment. The SmartDrive direct-drive motor fails differently from belt-drive washers — speed-dependent winding faults don't show up on standard motor testing. We use F&amp;P's diagnostic software to read the motor current profile at different RPMs before recommending motor vs controller replacement.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is Fisher &amp; Paykel owned by Haier?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes — Haier acquired 90% of Fisher &amp; Paykel in 2012. For repair purposes this improves parts availability for current models through Haier's supply chain. Legacy F&amp;P appliances (pre-2012) use original components available through the established F&amp;P service network. We service all generations.</div></div>
